com.microblink.recognizers.blinkid.mrtd

Interface MRTDDocumentClassifier

  • All Superinterfaces:
    android.os.Parcelable

    public interface MRTDDocumentClassifier
extends android.os.Parcelable
    Classifier that is used to classify Machine Readable Travel Documents based on data extracted from Machine Readable Zone. This is used to determine which set of decoding infos will be used to extract non-MRZ data.

    • Method Detail

      • classifyDocument

        java.lang.String classifyDocument(MRTDRecognitionResult mrzExtractionResult)
        Based on MRTDRecognitionResult classifies the MRTD document. For each MRTD document type that you want to support, returned result string has to be equal to the name of the corresponding set of DecodingInfo objects which are defined for that document type. Named decoding info sets should be defined using MRTDRecognizerSettings.setParserDecodingInfos(DecodingInfo[], String) method.
        Parameters:
        mrzExtractionResult - MRZ extraction result - contains only information extracted from Machine Readable Zone and from locations set with MRTDRecognizerSettings.setParserDecodingInfos(DecodingInfo[]).
        Returns:
        String identifying the MRTD document or null if document cannot be classified.
